@startuml
autonumber
actor "Prosumer / Utility Operator" as Actor
box "Orchestration Layer" #LightCyan
participant "Camunda Engine" as Camunda
participant "Kong Gateway" as Kong
end box

box "Microservice Layer" #LightYellow
participant "Prosumer MS" as PMS
participant "Utility Operator MS" as UOMS
end box

box "Data Layer" #LightGreen
database "AWS RDS \nProsumer" as DBp
database "AWS RDS \nUtility Operator" as DBu
end box

note over Actor, DBu: Deregistration process follows the same information flow but using different operators like DELETE and REMOVE 

== Prosumer Registration ==

Actor -> Camunda: Prosumer Register
Camunda -> Kong: POST /prosumer
Kong -> PMS: Forward Request
PMS -> DBp: JDBC INSERT: \n(Name, Fiscal ID, Location, Payment Details)
DBp --> PMS: 200 OK
PMS --> Kong: 201 Created
Kong --> Camunda: 201 Created
Camunda --> Actor: Sucessfull register 

== Utility Operator & Grid Zone Registration ==
Actor -> Camunda: Operator or \nGrid Zone Register
Camunda -> Kong: POST /utility-operator or \nPOST /GridZone
Kong -> UOMS: Forward Request
UOMS -> DBu: JDBC INSERT: \n(Creation, max capacity, geographic boundaries) \nor \nJDBC INSERT: \n(Name, Fiscal ID, Location, Payment Details)
DBu --> UOMS: 200 OK
UOMS --> Kong: 201 Created
Kong --> Camunda: 201 Created
Camunda --> Actor: Sucessfull register 
@enduml